</exercise><exercise id="fs-id832930" type="problems-exercises"><problem id="fs-id1261416"><para id="import-auto-id2758865">A nervous physicist worries that the two metal shelves of his wood frame bookcase might obtain a high voltage if charged by static electricity, perhaps produced by friction. (a) What is the capacitance of the empty shelves if they have area <m:math>
 <m:semantics>
  <m:mrow>
